entries.title: Jeff Beck, legendary rock guitarist and musician, dies at age 78
entries.description: Jeff Beck, the rock guitarist often regarded among the greatest of all-time, has died, according to a statement posted to his official social media accounts. He was 78.

entries.title: Dual British-Iranian citizen sentenced to death for spying for UK
entries.description: Alireza Akbari, a dual British-Iranian citizen and former Iranian official, has been sentenced to death in Iran for spying for the United Kingdom, according to Iranian judiciary-affiliated outlet Mizan on Wednesday.

entries.title: Tatjana Patitz, one of the original '90s supermodels, dies at 56
entries.description: Tatjana Patitz, who rose to fashion fame in the '90s as an animal-loving supermodel with a piercing gaze, has died, her agent confirmed to CNN. She was 56.

entries.title: Analysis: Gerasimov handed 'the most poisoned of chalices'
entries.description: Russia's Defense Ministry announced yet another realignment of the commanders leading the war in Ukraine on Wednesday, as criticism mounts over its handling of the stalled campaign.

entries.title: White House calls GOP probe into Biden family 'political stunt' to 'get attention on Fox'
entries.description: In one of his first moves as House Oversight Chairman, Rep. James Comer is seeking information from the Treasury Department about the Biden family's financial transactions and calling on a handful of former Twitter executives to testify at a public hearing. CNN's Sara Murray provides more details on the probe.

entries.title: A look at Putin's war and a $47B Russian deficit in 2022
entries.description: As the one-year mark of Russia's war in Ukraine grows closer, CNN's Clare Sebastian examines President Vladimir Putin's actions and the grave impacts on Russia's economy.

entries.title: Missing 5-year-old boy was pulled from mother's arms as California floodwater swept away their SUV
James Webb Space Telescope discovers its first exoplanet
entries.description: The James Webb Space Telescope can add another cosmic accomplishment to its list: The space observatory has been used to confirm the existence of an exoplanet for the first time.

entries.title: White House refuses to answer key questions about classified documents in Biden's private office
entries.description: The White House on Wednesday refused to answer a number of critical questions about the classified documents from Joe Biden's time as vice president discovered inside a private office last fall, citing an ongoing Department of Justice review.

entries.title: The mysteries of the bodies buried in Europe's bogs unraveled by new research
entries.description: In 1984, a peat cutter discovered human remains in a bog in Cheshire, England. They belonged to a man who died a brutal death some 2,100 years ago before being placed in the bog — examination of his well-preserved mummy revealed blows to the head, a possible stab wound and a broken neck. Twisted sinew found still wrapped around his neck may have also been a garotte.

entries.title: Watch reporters swarm George Santos as NY GOP leaders call for his resignation
entries.description: Leaders of the Nassau County Republican Party have called for Rep. George Santos, elected to represent New York's 3rd Congressional District in November, to resign from office over his lies to voters and fabrications about his personal life.

entries.title: Kate Winslet goes viral for giving child reporter pep talk
entries.description: A wholesome moment of actress Kate Winslet comforting a child reporter has gone viral and accumulated over a million views on Twitter. The Oscar winner is seen giving the young girl a pep talk ahead of her first interview which aired on CNN affiliate and German broadcaster ZDF.

entries.title: Tennis star Naomi Osaka announces she is pregnant
entries.description: Tennis star Naomi Osaka announced her pregnancy on social media Wednesday, tweeting a picture of an ultrasound scan along with a statement.

entries.title: 'A very significant emergency': California's deadly, record-setting storms are about to get an encore
entries.description: The historic storms devastating much of California have turned entire neighborhoods into lakes, unleashed sewage into floodwater and killed at least 17 people.

entries.title: Opinion: SE Cupp breaks down the key difference between Trump and Biden classified docs revelations
entries.description: In this week's episode of "Unfiltered," SE Cupp argues that while both President Joe Biden and former President Donald Trump were wrong for keeping classified documents in their personal possession, there is a huge difference in how they and their supporters have handled these revelations.

entries.title: Late night hosts react to classified documents found at Biden's former office
entries.description: Late night hosts poked fun at the reports that back in November President Biden's lawyers found government records, including classified documents, at a former office that he used when he was an honorary professor at the University of Pennsylvania.

entries.title: See moment snowboarder is swept away by avalanche
entries.description: Despite testing the snowpack beforehand, snowboarder Blake Nielson found himself being swept away by an avalanche during a run at Utah's Big Cottonwood Canyon. CNN affiliate KSL has the story.

entries.title: Macron is dragging France's retirement age out of the 17th century
entries.description: The last time President Emmanuel Macron tried to drag France's antiquated pension and retirement system from the 17th century into the 21st century with one long pull, mobs coursed through the streets of Paris, flaming barricades went up on the Champs Elysées and Macron's entire presidency nearly floundered in the face of the "gilets jaunes" (yellow vests).

entries.title: Judge will allow prosecutors to use Trump's 'stand back and stand by' comment in Proud Boys trial
entries.description: A federal judge ruled Wednesday that prosecutors can use video of then-President Donald Trump telling the far-right group the Proud Boys to "stand back and stand by" in the trial against several of the group's leaders charged with seditious conspiracy.

entries.title: Damar Hamlin has been released after spending more than a week hospitalized due to a cardiac arrest
entries.description: Damar Hamlin has been released after being hospitalized for more than a week due to a cardiac arrest he suffered during a "Monday Night Football" game earlier this month, the Buffalo Bills tweeted Wednesday.

entries.title: Skeleton of man who dreaded becoming a museum exhibit will finally be removed from display
entries.description: A British museum is to remove its most famous exhibit from display -- the skeleton of an 18th-century man popularly known as the "Irish Giant."

entries.title: 'I can't do that': Cop impressed by drunk driver's backflip
entries.description: This DWI suspect didn't flip out during traffic stop ... he BACKFLIPPED! CNN's Jeanne Moos has the bodycam video.

entries.title: Jerrod Carmichael burns Tom Cruise and Scientology with Shelly Miscavige joke
entries.description: Jerrod Carmichael had a pitch for Tom Cruise and Church of Scientology in one of his Golden Globes jokes.

entries.title: Yellen will remain Treasury secretary heading into the Biden administration's third year
entries.description: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen plans to stay in her Cabinet role heading into the third year of the administration, a decision she conveyed to President Joe Biden during a December conversation, according to two White House officials.

entries.title: Global experts worry simultaneous crises could become the new norm
entries.description: Business executives, politicians and academics are bracing for a gloomy world battered by intersecting crises, as rising volatility and depleted resilience boost the odds of painful simultaneous shocks.

entries.title: Netflix will stream a live awards show for the first time
entries.description: Netflix will air a live awards show for the first time, marking the streamer's latest expansion into live programming and further cementing its influence in Hollywood.

entries.title: Unusually brightening star captures attention as a stellar oddity
House Oversight chairman seeks Biden family financial transaction data
entries.description: Rep. James Comer, in one of his first moves as House Oversight Chairman, is seeking information from the Treasury Department about the Biden family's financial transactions and calling on a handful of former Twitter executives to testify at a public hearing.

entries.title: What is NOTAM, the FAA computer system that halted all US flights?
entries.description: A critical Federal Aviation Administration computer system that experienced an outage Wednesday and briefly halted all US flights provides airlines with a digital bulletin board of crucial safety updates.

entries.title: Atlético Madrid and Portugal forward João Félix joins Chelsea on loan until end of 2022/23 season
entries.description: Atlético Madrid and Portugal forward João Félix has joined Chelsea on loan until the end of the 2022/23 season, the English Premier League side announced on Wednesday.

entries.title: FAA lifts pause on flights after outage creates travel chaos
entries.description: • Flight departures paused until 9 a.m. ET

entries.title: Why is Russia so keen to capture the town of Soledar?
entries.description: Fighting is still raging in Soledar, a salt mine town in eastern Ukraine, despite Russian claims that it has gained control of the region.

entries.title: Ocean heat hits another record high in 2022, fueling extreme weather
entries.description: The world's oceans were the warmest on record for the fourth year in row in 2022, a troubling sign of the climate crisis caused by humans pumping heat-trapping gases into the atmosphere.

entries.title: 'More rain, more flood, more mud': California resident on storms pounding West Coast
entries.description: Response crews are busy clearing flooded neighborhoods and crumbled roadways after a powerful storm walloped California with heavy downpours and strong winds, forcing thousands of evacuations -- and more rain is on the way. CNN national correspondent Camlia Bernal reports.

entries.title: US and Japan to strengthen military relationship with upgraded Marine unit in attempt to deter China
entries.description: The US and Japan are set to announce a significant strengthening of their military relationship and upgrading of the US military's force posture in the country this week, including the stationing of a newly redesignated Marine unit with advanced intelligence, surveillance capabilities and the ability to fire anti-ship missiles, according to two US officials briefed on the matter.

entries.title: Executions aren't new in Iran, but this time they're different
entries.description: The Islamic Republic of Iran has long ranked among the world's top executioners. But with the recent death sentences handed out to protesters, critics say the regime has taken capital punishment to a new level.

entries.title: FAA pausing all US departures until 9 a.m. ET
Meet the group protecting patients from protesters outside abortion clinics
entries.description: When the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade in June, Planned Parenthood made a vow.

entries.title: Unusually brightening star captures attention as a stellar oddity
entries.description: Astronomers might have solved the mystery behind an unusually brightening star.

entries.title: Her alleged attacker is a suspected serial killer. She forgives him but not the police
entries.description: Her body is riddled with bullet hole scars and specks of shrapnel. Just beneath the skin on her waist and chest are two lumps of leftover ammunition. Yet Natasha LaTour is still alive -- believed to be the lone survivor of a suspected serial killer.

entries.title: Exclusive: Pepsi is ditching Sierra Mist for a new Sprite rival
entries.description: Pepsi is reaching for the stars in its latest effort to take on Sprite.

entries.title: Uganda's Ebola outbreak ends, leaving relief and unanswered questions
entries.description: No new Ebola infections have been detected in Uganda for 42 days, and so on Wednesday, the World the Health Organization and the Ugandan Ministry of Health officially declared that the country's most recent outbreak of the deadly virus is at an end.

entries.title: Passengers stuck on runway as their flight takes off without them
entries.description: A group of passengers at India's Bengaluru airport experienced a particular kind of flight envy as they watched their own plane take off without them.

entries.title: Uganda declares end of Ebola outbreak
entries.description: Ugandan authorities have officially declared the end of a recent Ebola outbreak after 42 consecutive days with no new cases.

entries.title: Investors are underestimating inflation again
entries.description: Investors are holding their breath in anticipation of Thursday morning's Consumer Price Index inflation report — arguably the most important piece of economic data so far this year.

entries.title: FAA system outage causes flight chaos across US
entries.description: A Federal Aviation Administration system that provides pilots with notices they need to read before flying is experiencing an outage, affecting flights in the United States.

entries.title: Peru's top prosecutor launches inquiry into president and top ministers after deadly protests
entries.description: Peru's top prosecutor's office on Tuesday said it has launched an inquiry into new President Dina Boluarte and members of her cabinet over violent clashes that have seen at least 40 killed and hundreds injured since early December.

entries.title: Ex-King Constantine II of Greece dies at 82
entries.description: The former King of Greece, Constantine II, has died at the age of 82, CNN affiliate CNN Greece reported on Tuesday.

entries.title: How this airport was transformed into a spaceport
entries.description: As Virgin Orbit undertook its latest satellite mission this week -- the sixth for the space exploration company -- the conditions were a little different from its usual US desert setting.

entries.title: Gwen Stefani faces criticism over "I'm Japanese" comment in Allure magazine interview
entries.description: Music star Gwen Stefani has been called out for comments made about her affinity to Japan during an interview with Allure magazine, while promoting her beauty brand GXVE.

entries.title: Demi Lovato poster banned by advertising regulator for being offensive to Christians
entries.description: Britain's advertising regulator has banned a poster promoting Demi Lovato's most recent album for being "likely to cause serious offence to Christians."

entries.title: 'That's crazy': Miami Heat set new NBA record for perfection, going 40/40 on free throws
entries.description: The Miami Heat set a new NBA record for perfection on Tuesday night, not missing a free throw during their win over the Oklahoma City Thunder at FTX Arena.

entries.title: Brazilian soccer star Dani Alves under investigation for alleged sexual assault
entries.description: Brazilian football player Dani Alves is under investigation for an alleged sexual assault that took place in Barcelona last month, the Catalonia Higher Court of Justice confirmed on Tuesday.

entries.title: After two surgeries and four rounds of chemotherapy, Sébastien Haller makes his Borussia Dortmund debut
entries.description: Sébastien Haller savored the "amazing" opportunity to play his first game for Borussia Dortmund on Tuesday after testicular cancer sidelined the striker for six months.

entries.title: Your attention span is shrinking, studies say. Here's how to stay focused
entries.description: I've been working steadily for hours now, but feel as if I haven't even started. My attention is being pulled from my assigned task — writing this story — by a myriad of what I believe are necessary work interruptions. (OK, a couple were from my cat, who also firmly believes in their necessity.)

entries.title: Afrofuturist artist creates photos of mysterious 'Humaliens'
entries.description: These photo portraits might look like designs for the next Star Wars film, but they are actually the vision of Ivorian artist and graphic designer Eric Adé Tanauh.

entries.title: Missing teenage girls in Pakistan ran away to meet BTS, police say
entries.description: Two teenage girls reported missing in Pakistan last week have been found more than 750 miles from home after attempting to travel to South Korea to meet K-pop super band BTS, police in the South Asian country said.

entries.title: As University of Idaho students return to classes, they say the arrest of a murder suspect brings peace of mind. But the campus may never feel the same
Egg prices 'expected to soar' in Japan after record cull of 10 million birds
entries.description: Japan has culled just under 10 million birds as it confronts a massive outbreak of avian flu, which is threatening to put further strain on poultry supply and increase the price of eggs.

entries.title: Soldier posts video showing intense fighting in strategic Ukrainian town
entries.description: Russian troops are focusing attention on Soledar — a salt mining town in eastern Ukraine. CNN's Scott McLean reports.

entries.title: There will be no third world war:' Zelensky's message of hope at the Golden Globes
Several people injured in knife attack at Paris central railway station, operator says
entries.description: Police opened fire on a "dangerous person" who injured travelers at one of Paris' main railway stations, Gare du Nord, on Wednesday, French rail operator SNCF tweeted.

entries.title: Russia appears to focus efforts on eastern town of Soledar
As Russia's military stalls, oligarch Yevgeny Prigozhin is fighting his own war with his Wagner mercenary group in eastern Ukraine
entries.description: • Artillery fire in Ukraine down nearly 75%, indicating Russia's weakening position

entries.title: Ryan Murphy honors LGBTQ actors in Golden Globes speech
entries.description: Ryan Murphy walked away from the 80th Golden Globe Awards with the Carol Barnett Award honoring his contributions to television. He used his acceptance speech to send an uplifting message to honor LGBTQ actors.

entries.title: Jailed Bolsonaro supporters are unrepenting in the aftermath of the January 8 riot
entries.description: A man clenched his fist as he squeezed his upper body through the small window of a bus leaving the Brazilian Federal Police Headquarters in Brasilia on Tuesday.

entries.title: The Golden Globes return, honoring 'The Fabelmans' and 'Banshees' while addressing its controversy
entries.description: Steven Spielberg's autobiographical "The Fabelmans" and the understated Irish period piece "The Banshees of Inisherin" claimed the top prizes at the Golden Globe Awards, on a night that saw the event return to television and directly address the controversy that prompted its TV absence in 2022.

entries.title: Full list of winners
entries.description: The 80th Golden Globes Awards are being presented Tuesday.

entries.title: Stephanie McMahon resigns as WWE's chairwoman and co-CEO
entries.description: Four days after her disgraced father returned to WWE's board, the wrestling company's co-CEO and chairwoman Stephanie McMahon resigned from the company.

entries.title: The owner of Uniqlo is boosting pay for Japan employees by up to 40% as inflation bites
entries.description: Fast Retailing, the Japanese giant that owns popular clothing brands Uniqlo and Theory, will start paying its employees much more this year.

entries.title: She's the first MCU performer to win an acting Golden Globe for her role in 'Black Panther: Wakanda Forever'
See who won at the Golden Globes
Philippine top court voids old South China Sea energy deal
entries.description: The Supreme Court in the Philippines on Tuesday declared the country's 2005 energy exploration agreement with Chinese and Vietnamese firms was illegal, ruling the constitution does not allow foreign entities to exploit natural resources.

entries.title: Isa Soares speaks with an arrested Bolsanaro supporter
entries.description: CNN's Isa Soares speaks to one of the more than 1,500 supporters of former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro who were detained after breaking into the nation's Congress, Supreme Court and Presidential Palace.

entries.title: Rocket aiming to launch satellites explodes off Alaska's coast
entries.description: A rocket operated by a California-based start-up failed near the coast of Alaska Tuesday, marking yet another mishap for companies hoping to offer their services to launch scores of small satellites into orbit.

entries.title: Golden Globes: Stars start to arrive on red carpet
Biden explains what happened with classified documents found in private office
entries.description: While meeting with Mexican President Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau, President Joe Biden explained what happened with the classified documents found in his private office from his time as Vice President and said he is cooperating with the review by the DOJ.
